Moses Clemente, 47, was shot in the abdomen. He is in critical condition at Trinity Mother Frances hospital but is expected to recover.

The shooting occurred at 6am on Sunday after Maples saw his wife's vehicle at the home and entered through an unlocked door.

Maples called 911 after the shooting to tell police he had shot his wife and her boyfriend.

Heather Maples and Clemente had a relationship before she married Larry Maples, authorities said.

Sheriff Ray told Kltv: 'This is a senseless murder that will no doubt affect many people in our community, especially his family, and my heart goes out to this family.'

